track_notes: Trailhead parking is just before a gated community entrance on Mountain Parkway.  The parking area is closed during the night, when I hiked it opened at 5:00 am which was shorty after twilight.  The first half mile is on sidewalk into the community and then the next couple of miles are on nice single-track trail that takes you to the old Dixie Mine.  The final couple of miles are up a 4wd road and it becomes extremely steep near the top.
track_title: Thompson Peak via Dixie Mine Trail

track_notes: I took my mountain bike up Thompson Peak. I rode the hiking trail in but came out the Thompson Peak Road. The Thompson Peak road is a much better and easier mountain bike route. I recommend that route for both up and down if youre on a bike. Its longer, but much easier to ride. When I got to the steep section, I pushed my bike...all the way to the summit. It was strenuous, but I figured the ride down would be worth it. Its probably an expert ride because its so steep. But its not very technical. Just steep. I think it reaches 35 degrees or more in short stretches. It took me 2.5 hours to ride and hike up and 30 minutes to ride out. You can park at the Golden Eagle park. Good cell signal on top. Hi Hi. Make sure you have disc breaks and that they are in good shape.
